fdd:citation.fdd:specReference:
ISO/IEC 15444-10:2008. 
Information technology -- JPEG 2000 image coding system: Extensions for three-dimensional data. Part 10: defines a set of lossless (bit-preserving) and lossy compression methods for coding continuous-tone, bi-level, grey-scale, colour digital volumetric images, or multi-component volumetric images. This set of methods extends the elements in the core coding system defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 and ISO/IEC 15444-2. . . .  ISO/IEC 15444-10:2008 also defines extensions to the compressed data format, i.e. interchange format and the abbreviated formats.

In particular, for ISO/IEC 15444-2, the following extensions are supported by ISO/IEC 15444-10:2008:
variable DC offset; arbitrary wavelet transform kernels; multi-component transformations;
non-linear transformations;
region-of-interest.
